-- Sarkozy Gaining on Hollande in French Vote, LH2-Yahoo Poll Shows
-- B y   C a r o l   M a t l a c k
-- 2012-03-18T10:55:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/sarkozy-gaining-on-hollande-in-french-vote-lh2-yahoo-poll-shows.html
Socialist Francois Hollande’s lead
over  Nicolas Sarkozy  has been cut to 3 percentage points in the
first round of French presidential voting and to 10 points in
the second round, according to a poll by LH2 for Yahoo.  The poll, conducted March 16 and 17 and released today,
shows Hollande winning 30.5 percent in the first round on April
22, with Sarkozy at 27.5 percent. Hollande’s support held steady
since a previous survey on March 4, while Sarkozy gained 4.5
percentage points, according to a news release by LH2.  Hollande would win the May 6 second round 55 percent to 45
percent, the release said. His support declined 3 percentage
points from the March 4 survey, while Sarkozy’s gained 3 points.
The poll questioned 962 people and has a margin of error of plus
or minus 3.5 percentage points for the first round and 4 points
for the second round, the release said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
